      • contains

        public boolean contains(T data)
        Checks the table to see if a row with the data specified exists. NOTE: The data in the table should have a valid and appropriate equals method to compare data.
        Parameters:
        data - The data that will be used to check the table for.
        Returns:
        True if there is a matching data piece to a row in the table, false otherwise.

      • difference

        Parameters:
        table - The table used to compare with the original one.
        Returns:

                   Table<T> table)
        Creates a new table comprised of nodes having a value for a specific attribute, created from two tables.
        Parameters:
        attribute - The attribute to restrict to.
        value - The value of that attribute to restrict to.
        table - The other table to compare with.
